annotationA: Ribosomal protein L35, isoform A; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; centrosome duplication; mitotic spindle organization
annotationB: Signal recognition particle 54 kDa protein; Binds to the signal sequence of presecretory protein when they emerge from the ribosomes and transfers them to TRAM (translocating chain-associating membrane protein); Belongs to the GTP-binding SRP family. SRP54 subfamily
